AgreementRegistry_createAgreement
├── when msg.sender is address(0)
│   └── it should revert with InvalidParty
├── when partyB is address(0)
│   └── it should revert with InvalidParty
├── when msg.sender equals partyB
│   └── it should revert with PartiesIdentical
└── when parties are valid
    ├── it should create an agreement-level hat (child of top hat)
    ├── it should deploy an Agreement clone via Clones.cloneDeterministic
    ├── it should use salt = keccak256(abi.encode(agreementHatId, block.chainid))
    ├── it should mint the agreement hat to the new agreement contract
    ├── it should register the agreement as a minter on ResourceTokenRegistry
    ├── it should initialize the agreement with parties, agreementHatId, and proposalData
    ├── it should store the agreement → hatId mapping
    ├── it should set the agreement state to PROPOSED
    ├── it should set turn to partyB
    ├── it should emit AgreementCreated with creator = msg.sender
    └── it should return the agreement address

AgreementRegistry_createAgreement_deterministic
├── given the same agreementHatId and chainId
│   └── it should deploy to a deterministic address
└── given a different agreementHatId (new agreement between same parties)
    └── it should deploy to a different address

AgreementRegistry_agreementHatIds
├── given agreement has not been created
│   └── it should return 0
└── given agreement has been created
    └── it should return the agreement-level hat ID

AgreementRegistry_constructor
├── it should store the hats address
├── it should store the topHatId
├── it should store the resourceTokenRegistry address
└── it should store the agreementImplementation address
